pgbackrest (2.12-1) unstable; urgency=medium

    pgBackRest no longer supports dots in S3 bucket names.

    The new TLS/SSL implementation forbids dots in S3 bucket names per
    RFC-2818. This security fix is required for compliant hostname
    verification.

 -- Adrian Vondendriesch <adrian.vondendriesch@credativ.de>  Sat, 13 Apr 2019 17:12:58 +0200

pgbackrest (2.04-1) unstable; urgency=medium

    Critical Bug Fix for Backup Resume:
    This release fixes a critical bug in the backup resume feature. All
    resumed backups prior to this release should be considered inconsistent.
    A backup will be resumed after a prior backup fails, unless resume=n has
    been specified. A resumed backup can be identified by checking the backup
    log for the message "aborted backup of same type exists, will be cleaned
    to remove invalid files and resumed". If the message exists, do not use
    this backup or any backup in the same set for a restore and check the
    restore logs to see if a resumed backup was restored. If so, there may be
    inconsistent data in the cluster.

 -- Adrian Vondendriesch <adrian.vondendriesch@credativ.de>  Fri, 06 Jul 2018 11:43:36 +0200
